exav — THIRD-PARTY NOTICES
==========================

exav itself is licensed under the MIT License (see the LICENSE file).

The exav binary statically links a number of third-party Rust crates. Those
crates retain their own licenses; the binary distribution must carry their
notices. This file enumerates the major components and reproduces the notice
texts that the BSD-3-Clause and Apache-2.0-WITH-LLVM-exception licenses require.

This is a hand-maintained summary of the principal components, not a byte-exact
dump of every transitive crate's license. To regenerate a complete, per-crate
attribution list from the resolved dependency graph, install one of:

    cargo install cargo-about        # then: cargo about generate about.hbs
    cargo install cargo-bundle-licenses

and run it against this workspace. `cargo deny check licenses` (run in CI)
confirms every dependency resolves to a permissive license on the allowlist in
deny.toml.

Versions below reflect Cargo.lock at the time of writing.


