1d. ppmd-rust PPMd7 (var.H) model — CC0-1.0 OR MIT-0 (source derivative)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The PPMd variant H decoder in crates/exav-unpack/src/formats/ppmd7/ is vendored
and adapted from the `ppmd-rust` crate (version 1.4.0), generalised over a range
decoder trait so it can be driven by either the 7-Zip or the RAR range coder.
`ppmd-rust` is dual-licensed CC0-1.0 OR MIT-0 (public-domain-equivalent) and is
itself a Rust port of Igor Pavlov's 7-Zip PPMd7, which implements
Dmitry Shkarin's public-domain PPMd var.H (2001). It does NOT derive from
UnRAR/RARLAB.

Upstream: https://crates.io/crates/ppmd-rust
License: CC0-1.0 OR MIT-0 (https://spdx.org/licenses/CC0-1.0,
         https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT-0). Both place the work in (or treat it
         as) the public domain; no attribution is legally required, and this
         entry is recorded for completeness.

The RAR-specific framing wired into crates/exav-unpack/src/formats/rar3_unpack.rs
(the PPMd block header: order/sub-allocator-memory/escape bits; the RAR
Subbotin carry-less range decoder in ppmd7/rangedec.rs; and the escape-symbol
handling for the PPMd↔LZSS conversion) is reproduced from the public format
description in libarchive's BSD-2-Clause archive_read_support_format_rar.c /
archive_ppmd7.c (already attributed in section 1b above), NOT from UnRAR.


