4. MIT / Apache-2.0 dual-licensed components (the bulk of the graph)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The majority of exav's dependencies are dual-licensed "MIT OR Apache-2.0" (or a
superset including Unlicense / 0BSD / Zlib), so the MIT or Apache terms apply at
the distributor's choice. Notable examples:

  aho-corasick, memchr, daachorse        pattern matching / Aho-Corasick
  serde, rmp-serde                       serialization
  clap                                   CLI parsing
  sha1, sha2, md-5, digest (RustCrypto)  hashing
  flate2, miniz_oxide, xz2, bzip2,       decompression
    sevenz-rust2, zip
  walkdir                                directory traversal
  regex                                  path-filter regexes
  libc                                   syscall bindings (daemon)

RustCrypto crates are MIT OR Apache-2.0. Zlib-licensed components present:
miniz_oxide, zlib-rs, tinyvec, foldhash. Unicode-3.0: the ICU / unicode-ident
crates. Other permissive licenses in the graph: CC0-1.0 and MIT-0 (ppmd-rust via
sevenz-rust2), CDLA-Permissive-2.0 (webpki-roots, TLS root store), bzip2-1.0.6
(libbz2-rs-sys).

Full MIT and Apache-2.0 license texts are widely available and are reproduced in
each crate's source distribution; the exav LICENSE file contains the MIT text.
